ce:section.ce:para:
A UV–vis spectrophotometer with an integrating sphere was used to measure the transmittance (T) and haze (H) of the films. The test covered a wavelength range from 200 to 800 nm with 1 nm intervals. Data were collected with and without the sample and reflective plate as follows:
T
1 : Transmittance without a sample and with a reflective plate, representing the incident luminous flux of the instrument;
T
2 : Transmittance with a sample and a reflective plate, representing the total transmitted luminous flux passing through the film;
T
3 : Transmittance without a sample or reflective plate, representing the scattered luminous flux of the instrument;
T
4 : Transmittance with a sample and without a reflective plate, representing the total scattered luminous flux of both the sample and the instrument.
